@startuml
[*] --> Start: Initial State
State "Start" as start
start --> AddGoods: The system shall allow the user to add new goods to the inventory.*
start --> UpdatePrice: The system shall allow the user to update the price of existing items in the inventory.
start --> RemoveGoods: The system shall allow the user to remove goods from the inventory that are no longer required.*

State "Add Goods" as add_goods
add_goods --> AddGoodsSuccess: Successful addition of new goods.*
add_goods --> AddGoodsFailure: Failed to add new goods.*

State "Update Price" as update_price
update_price --> UpdatePriceSuccess: Successful price update.*
update_price --> UpdatePriceFailure: Failed to update price.*

State "Remove Goods" as remove_goods
remove_goods --> RemoveGoodsSuccess: Successful removal of goods.*
remove_goods --> RemoveGoodsFailure: Failed to remove goods.*

start --> IdentifyExpiredGoods: The system shall identify expired goods and notify the user about their removal from the inventory.
start --> PlaceOrder: The system shall allow the user to place an order to a supplier for additional goods when required.

State "Place Order" as place_order
place_order --> PlaceOrderSuccess: Successful placement of order.*
place_order --> PlaceOrderFailure: Failed to place order.*

start --> SearchItems: The system shall allow the user to search for items available in the inventory and select them for purchase.
start --> GenerateInvoice: The system shall generate an invoice for the order once it is placed.

State "Search Items" as search_items
search_items --> SearchItemsSuccess: Successful search of items.*
search_items --> SearchItemsFailure: Failed to search items.*

State "Generate Invoice" as generate_invoice
generate_invoice --> GenerateInvoiceSuccess: Successful generation of invoice.*
generate_invoice --> GenerateInvoiceFailure: Failed to generate invoice.*

start --> CalculateDiscountTax: The system shall calculate the applicable discount and tax based on the selected items.
start --> GenerateReceipt: The system shall generate a receipt for the customer after the purchase.

State "Calculate Discount Tax" as calculate_discount_tax
calculate_discount_tax --> CalculateDiscountTaxSuccess: Successful calculation of discount and tax.*
calculate_discount_tax --> CalculateDiscountTaxFailure: Failed to calculate discount and tax.*

State "Generate Receipt" as generate_receipt
generate_receipt --> GenerateReceiptSuccess: Successful generation of receipt.*
generate_receipt --> GenerateReceiptFailure: Failed to generate receipt.*

start --> ReplaceItemCancelReceipt: The system shall allow the user to replace an item or cancel the receipt during the billing process if needed.
start --> RecordCustomerRequests: The system shall record customer requests for items that may not be currently available.

State "Replace Item Cancel Receipt" as replace_item_cancel_receipt
replace_item_cancel_receipt --> ReplaceItemCancelReceiptSuccess: Successful replacement of item or cancellation of receipt.*
replace_item_cancel_receipt --> ReplaceItemCancelReceiptFailure: Failed to replace item or cancel receipt.*

State "Record Customer Requests" as record_customer_requests
record_customer_requests --> RecordCustomerRequestsSuccess: Successful recording of customer requests.*
record_customer_requests --> RecordCustomerRequestsFailure: Failed to record customer requests.*

start --> ViewSummaryReport: The system shall allow the user to view a summary report of all transactions carried out in the system at any point.

State "View Summary Report" as view_summary_report
view_summary_report --> ViewSummaryReportSuccess: Successful viewing of summary report.*
view_summary_report --> ViewSummaryReportFailure: Failed to view summary report.*

@enduml
